<TITLE> 3 arrested for possession of Phensidyle </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)  Three men were arrested for possessing 1599 bottles of Phensidyle from Shibganj upazila in Chapainawabganj. Rapid Action Battalion and Bangladesh Rifles initiated the drive Thursday night and detained Mohammad Morsalin, 30, of Shialmara village and Babul Mia, 44, and Sabbir Hossain, 30, of Chandpur Hazardighi village of the upazila. OC of Shibganj Police Station Anwar Hossain told bdnews24.com that RAB had seized 989 bottles of Phensidyle and arrested Morsalin in the drive conducted at North Makimpur area on Thursday midnight. In another drive at around 2:30am in Chandpur Hazarbighi area, he said, the BDR members had seized another 610 bottles of Phencidyl and arrested Babul and Sabbir. Anwar said two separate cases were filed against the arrested under drug control law. bdnews24.
